<item>
            <title>[FLINK-36533] Fix detecting bind failure in case of Netty EPOLL transport</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-36533</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;An error occurred when using a port range for the &lt;tt&gt;taskmanager.data.bind-port&lt;/tt&gt; configuration item.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Environment Information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Flink version: 1.20.0&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Java: 1.8&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Configuration Information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;taskmanager.data.bind-port: 12001-13000&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;When starting the Flink job, an exception occurs. Please see the attached file for the exception message: exception.png&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The error received is a NativeIoException. However, the source code is set up to catch a BindException. (Refer to the attached file: source_code.png) The two do not match.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
