                            <comment id="17889495" author="JIRAUSER306586" created="Tue, 15 Oct 2024 07:09:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We hit the same issue described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-18383&quot; title=&quot;Utils.isBindCollision does not properly handle all possible address-port collisions when binding&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-18383&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-18383&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. In case of &quot;epoll&quot; Netty transport (which is a Linux-only feature), Netty uses different sockets and throws a different exception type in case of a used address. Will raise a PR shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
